  "text": "While such results seem promising in many ways, GSK3 is important for normal human physiology; as its name implies, it is critical to proper glycogen metabolism. Moreover, a selective GSK3 inhibitor was found to cause neurodegeneration in healthy wild-type mice [CITATION_1] , suggesting that at least some level of GSK3 activity is essential to neuronal function. erefore, although abnormally high GSK3 activity is associated with several different diseases (diabetes, cancer, and bipolar disorder) and GSK3 appears to be a promising target, complete inhibition is apparently not desirable.",
