      "span_text": "Moreover, a selective GSK3 inhibitor was found to cause neurodegeneration in healthy wild-type mice [CITATION_1] , suggesting that at least some level of GSK3 activity is essential to neuronal function. erefore, although abnormally high GSK3 activity is associated with several different diseases (diabetes, cancer, and bipolar disorder) and GSK3 appears to be a promising target, complete inhibition is apparently not desirable.",
